            . I am a <rs id="t18240916-245-viclabel1309" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-245-victim2048 t18240916-245-viclabel1309"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18240916-245-crimeloc1310">Brewer-street, Somers-town</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240916-245-crimeloc1310" type="placeName" value="Brewer-street, Somers-town"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240916-245-crimeloc1310" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-245-off1307 t18240916-245-crimeloc1310"></join>. On the 27th of August, about twelve o'clock I lost twelve yards of muslin - I had just brought them home and marked them. I left them on the counter, and went into the garden - my wife called me back, I came, and found some of my goods were gone. I followed the prisoner, and overtook her about fifty or sixty yards off. I charged her with the robbery; she said she had not got any thing. I told her to come back, and the piece of muslin fell from her in walking - it was one of those I had just brought home. She broke from me, I called Stop thief! and she was taken in my sight.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-245-person2050">
                  JAMES 
                  FOLKES
               <interp inst="t18240916-245-person2050" type="surname" value="FOLKES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-245-person2050" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-245-person2050" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a milkman. When the prisoner got from Mr. Noble, I stopped her.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A woman came up and asked if I would have any thing to drink, I said No; she said</p>
               <p>"Will you come with me to get a couple of shirts made." I took hold of the article, and this gentleman came and took me. I never denied having it, but gave it him directly.</p>
